    <name>Prepare for Session 4.5</name>
    <intro>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;In Session 4.5, we will look at a formative assessment lesson on solving linear equations. To prepare, complete the task &lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/When%20are%20the%20equations%20true.pdf?time=1688765854203" target="_blank" title="PDF - opens in a new window"&gt;When are the equations true?&lt;/a&gt;, which is typically given to learners a few days before the formative assessment lesson.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;In this task, learners respond to mathematical statements made by fictitious characters. The expectation is for learners to spend about 15&amp;nbsp;minutes on this task. They should not worry too much if they don’t understand or can’t do everything because,
    in the lesson from which this task is excerpted, learners engage in additional tasks to support the development of their understanding of algebraic equations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should spend about 15&amp;nbsp;minutes working on the task&lt;/strong&gt;, as your learners would; don’t worry if you do not complete it in that time.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;When you have finished, click the ADD SUBMISSION button below to submit your work. You may upload photos or a document. Remember to click SAVE CHANGES, then click SUBMIT ASSIGNMENT when you are done.&lt;/p&gt;</intro>
